President Muhammadu Buhari congratulated the minister of Education, Malam Adamu Adamu, as he marked his 67th birthday. Buhari in a statement by his media aide, Garba Shehu said from his decades-long association with Adam, a close associate, some of the characteristics that mark him (Adamu) out of the crowd are “his insightful ideas and motivational thoughts.” The president said he is pleased that the country’s education sector is moving ahead with energy, innovation and excellence due to the minister’s strong qualities. “Happy Birthday to our respectable minister of Education, wishing you many more happy returns of the day!” said the President